                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The Targets were Placed Between Two Summed Na-I(TL)",
                "Detectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Targets of Li-6 Fluoride, Ranging in Thickness",
                "Between 650 and 800 Microgram/Cm**2. Li-6 Fluoride,",
                "Of 99.32% Li-6 Enrichment, was Evaporated onto",
                "Aluminium Disks."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "SITA",
                "EDEG",
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Irradiations were Carried Out with a 6.0 MeV",
                "Li-6 Ion Beam. Lower Energies were Obtained by",
                "Al-Degrader Foils. Range and Stopping-Power Data",
                "For Li-6 in Al were Taken from Northcliffe and",
                "Schilling, Nucl.Data Tables A7,233(1970).",
                "Similar Data For Li-6 in Li-Fluoride by",
                "P.G.Steward, Report Ucrl-18127(BERKELY,1968).",
                "The be-7 Activity was Compared with a be-7",
                "Reference Standard, Calibrated on a Geli-Detector",
                "With Known Efficiency."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Measured be-7 Activities of the Foils were",
                "Corrected Back to the Time of Irradiation.",
                "A Production of be-7 Due to Reactions with",
                "Li-7, F-19 and Al-27 was Negligible. Corrections in",
                "The Energy Scale Due to the Energy Loss of Li-6 in the",
                "Target Result in an Energy Shift of the Experimental",
                "Points."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The Errors of the Cross Sections are 5-10%.",
                "The Main Contributions to the Standard Error are",
                "Uncertainties in the Calibration of the Reference",
                "Standard (+-3%), in the Beam Charge Collected (+-1%),",
                "In the Target Thicknesses (+- 1%), and Statistical",
                "Errors in the Target Activities (+-1%)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Given Cross Sections are Weighted-Average",
                "Values Obtained from an Error-Weighted Average of",
                "Two Determinations at Each Incident Energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
